                <head type="article" tid="30">Buddha and Bodhisattva Qualities</head>
                <div type="section" xml:id="EFT-KB-BUDDHA-BODHISATTVA-QUALITIES-article-1">
                    <p tid="6">See also marks and signs.txt (copied below) </p>
                    <p tid="7">Uttaratantra </p>
                    <p tid="8">PPs </p>
                    <p tid="9">Ratnamegha: bsvs 1.­243 et seq, buddhas 1.­247 et seq. </p>
                    <p tid="10">Scriptural sources for 32 major and 80 minor marks </p>
                    <p tid="11">PP: </p>
                    <p tid="12">Ch 63 of 100,000 </p>
                    <p tid="13">Ch 62 of 25,000 </p>
                    <p tid="14">Ch 73 of 18,000 </p>
                    <p tid="15">Chs 2 and 29 of 10,000 </p>
                    <p tid="16">Abhisamayālaṃkāra VIII.12-32 </p>
                    <p tid="17">Spuṭārtha </p>
                    <p tid="18">Lalitavistara (Toh 95) 7.98-103 </p>
                    <p tid="19">also 26.145-173 (32 marks with their “causes”). </p>
                    <p tid="20">Mahāyānodapeśa (Toh 169) vol.59, F.297a et seq. (32 marks with their “causes”) </p>
                    <p tid="21">Rāṣṭrapālaparipṛcchā (Toh 62) Ch 2. </p>
                    <p tid="22">Raśmisamantamukha (Toh 55) F.219a et seq. ?? </p>
                    <p tid="23">Ratnagotravibhāga-Uttaratantraśāstra III.17-25 (32 major only) </p>
                    <p tid="24">Mahāvastu </p>
                    <p tid="25">Pali: </p>
                    <p tid="26">Lakkhaṇasutta </p>
                    <p tid="27">others? </p>
                    <p tid="28">Note for # 77 of minor marks in PP 10k: </p>
                    <p tid="29">In the context of the 80 minor marks, the palms and soles are said in many such lists to be marked with auspicious symbols such as the svastika and śrīvatsa. This is
                        presumably in addition to the thousand-spoked wheels mentioned above and in most lists of the 32 major marks. The mention of the palm and sole markings in lists of the 32 major
                        marks in the Lalitavistara and Rāṣṭrapālaparipṛcchā both mention svastikas in addition to wheels. In the list of the 80 minor marks in the Lalitavistara (7.103), however, the
                        equivalent to this mention of markings on the palms and soles refers instead to Prince Siddhartha’s hair as curling into shapes such as the svastika and śrīvatsa. </p>
                </div>
